snippet.textDisplay:
Jack, btw, I think you're doing a great job as a Youtuber. I don't know you personally, but I'm glad that things are turning out better for you.

By the way, for anyone else going through difficult things like depression, anxiety, or otherwise, it sounds cliché, but you're not alone. You're not alone in your life, in your experiences, you're not alone. And if you think no one would care if you were gone, believe me when I say, people would care. So whatever is bugging you, talk about it. Scream about it. Write it out, do something. See someone. But don't bottle up your emotions. I've been there, and it is not a happy road, so let it out. I'm not a professional, but if you're able to, try to seek professional help. There are people who care. There are people who will help. And there are people who love you.

snippet.textDisplay: I'm an optimist by nature but last year I had a big breakdown and, similar to Jack, the bad thoughts made me snap and think "this is not myself, I don't want this for myself". It actually happened two weeks after I had started therapy, which I started because I was feeling so empty and I thought there was something wrong with me. Now I look back and laugh at myself then for thinking I was doing things wrong or that something was wrong with me. My mind was playing tricks due to my home environment and life (in retrospective) wasn't half as bad as I believed it was. Thanks to therapy I slowly learnt how to understand and deal with different situations from life. I'm 25 years old. Still going to therapy. It's so helpful!

First, thank you for the open, honesty. Even being a big YouTube name it's hard to open up to people sometimes. Shoutout to everyone who has pushed through their tough times and made it to 2020. I hope you have many more years to come.
Also I hate when people assume you can't be nice in person. My work is different, but I go to work at a nursing home and try to be a cheerful person, especially around my residents, and people think I'm fake because "no one can be that happy all the time." Like I try to live by your day is as good as you make it...

snippet.textDisplay: I know most people probably won’t care about what I have to say but I’m feeling the first 7 minutes of this video so fucking much, recently I was diagnosed with depression and anxiety which changed everything. It’s a constant thing that makes me feel like a failure and as though no one would ever miss me in a million years. I feel so numb all the time and even when I go to college to do stuff I love it’s like all of the feeling has been sucked out of it. I’ve thought about suicide, I’ve self harmed, I’ve pushed people away and shut myself down emotionally because I thought it was the best way to cope and a part of me still does, certain people in my life aren’t helping me and some people are. What I’m trying to say is that we’re all still fighting these urges no matter how big or small they might be and it’s going to take a long time to defeat them with or without any help so we shouldn’t have to suffer alone or have to apologise for being human. Just remember that Jack, you are loved by so many and so much. More than I could ever hope to be.

I know the may be comments like this but I would still like to share this

I'm very lonely even now as I'm writing this I'm very lonely. Ever heard about feeling lonely in a crowd, that's exactly what it is. snippet.textDisplay: Well since we are on the topic or dark thoughts I think I'm going to talk about mine so basically let's say I have about 15irl real friends and I do help them if they ask for help if I can but I have never seen them helping me when I really need someone just to talk to some of them even make fun of my problems some of them did care but never tried to comfort me and make me happier instead acted they are ignoring me thinking I would be better soon (although they might just didn't know what to say so those guys were best of my friends I would say) so I started feeling lonely over time and that made think of killing myself many times cus I thought if everyone acts like this then would anyone care if we're them then I will more happy than sad right?  Not to mention school bullies that always took me as a target for being weak and not popular and on top of that my dad wasn't really that type of dad who you can talk to cus he sometimes scares you away and mostly closed minded the only one that did truly think about me was my mom bless her heart for being such caring mother but all of this overwhelmed me that I was so sick mental but I think I'm going through some progress cus I started to make ppl listen and open up more and distance myself from the fake friends

snippet.textDisplay: Jack. I'm gonna be honest. On your channel I have been a fan for a while. I kinda watch your vids in and out. Just sometimes I watch to make my worries go away and I can tell that you are great person! Keep it up. Over the past few years I have dealt with a lot of depression and anxiety, insecurities. Suicidal thoughts. But youtubers like you who have dealt with the same problems in their life just makes me smile. Because I feel like I'm not alone. And though I actively struggle, it just makes me feel happier. Have a great day, week, month, year, and life. I know it's a screen. But it means more to me. So I guess I'm a few words, Thank you and everyone else on this platform ❤
